  ;;
  ;; ── Design notes ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  ;;
  (text "HUB75 LEVEL SHIFTER NOTES (IPC-2221B):\n\nU2 / U3 VCC = +5V_EXT_HUB75 (NOT +3V3)\n  74HCT inputs: VIH min = 2.0V — 3.3V logic drives them reliably\n  74HCT outputs swing to VCC (5V) — required for HUB75 panel\n  Do NOT power from +3V3: outputs would be 3.3V, unreliable with some panels\n\nDIR pin (pin 1) = GND on both U2 and U3\n  0Ω resistor or direct connection acceptable\n  Makes direction fixed A→B (3.3V in, 5V out)\n  Do NOT leave DIR floating\n\n~OE pin (pin 19) = GND on both U2 and U3\n  Always-enabled. No dynamic enable needed for HUB75.\n\nBYPASS CAPACITORS (IPC-2221B §6.3.3):\n  100nF 0402 X7R on each VCC pin\n  Place within 2mm of pin 20 on PCB\n  Via directly to GND plane — no trace between cap GND and via\n\nRETURN CURRENT PATH (IPC-2221B §6.2.3):\n  GND pins on J1 (pins 4, 8, 14, 16) must stitch directly to GND plane\n  Signal traces from U2/U3 outputs to J1 must have unbroken GND plane beneath\n  Do NOT route other signals between U2/U3 and J1 on the same layer"
    (at 20 145 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top)))
)
